  <div class="container" style="padding:3rem 1rem;display:grid;grid-template-columns:2fr 1fr;gap:2.5rem;max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div>
      <section id="about" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:1rem;color:#003087;">About PTCL — Pakistan Telecommunication Company</h2>
        <p>Pakistan Telecommunication Company Limited (PTCL) is Pakistan's largest integrated telecom company and the sole provider of fixed-line (PSTN) telephone services nationwide. Privatized in 2005 with Etisalat (UAE) acquiring a 26% stake, PTCL remains majority government-owned (51% Government of Pakistan). PTCL serves millions of households and businesses across <strong>2,000+ cities and towns</strong> with landline, DSL broadband, FlashFiber (fiber-optic), and CharJi wireless broadband services.</p>
<p>PakistanBill.online is <strong>Pakistan's only platform</strong> covering every utility bill — electricity, gas, water, and telecom — all in one place. No other website offers this. Check your <a href="/lesco-bill/">LESCO electricity bill</a> if you're in Lahore, <a href="/iesco-bill/">IESCO bill</a> in Islamabad, or <a href="/k-electric-bill/">K-Electric bill</a> in Karachi. For gas, check <a href="/sngpl-bill/">SNGPL</a> or <a href="/ssgc-bill/">SSGC</a>. See all providers in our <a href="/telecom/">telecom bills hub</a>, or learn <a href="/blog/change-name-ptcl-bill/">how to change name on your PTCL bill</a>.</p>
        <p>PTCL's product portfolio includes: <strong>PSTN landline</strong> (traditional copper phone line), <strong>DSL broadband</strong> (internet via existing phone line), <strong>FlashFiber</strong> (fiber-optic up to 1 Gbps — available in major cities), <strong>CharJi</strong> (4G LTE wireless broadband for areas without fixed infrastructure), and <strong>EVO</strong> (3G wireless broadband). All services under your account appear on a single monthly PTCL bill.</p>
        <p>PTCL's online bill portal <strong>dbill.ptcl.net.pk</strong> is unique among Pakistan's utility providers because it requires <strong>no CAPTCHA and no login</strong> — simply enter your phone number or Account ID to view your bill instantly.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="how-to" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:1rem;color:#003087;">How to Check PTCL Bill Online — Step by Step</h2>
        <ol style="line-height:2.5;padding-left:1.5rem;">
          <li>Find your <strong>PTCL telephone number</strong> (without area code) OR your <strong>10-digit Account ID</strong> from any previous bill</li>
          <li>Enter it in the tool at the top of this page, or visit <strong>dbill.ptcl.net.pk</strong> directly</li>
          <li>Click Submit — your PTCL bill appears with amount, due date, and all charge breakdowns</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Print Bill</strong> and select Save as PDF to download your duplicate bill</li>
          <li>Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, bank app, or online at ptcl.com.pk</li>
        </ol>
        <div style="background:#eff6ff;border-left:4px solid #003087;padding:1rem 1.5rem;border-radius:8px;margin-top:1rem;">
          <strong>💡 Important:</strong> PTCL's grace period is <strong>15 days</strong> after the due date — the longest of any Pakistani utility. However, pay on time to avoid any service disruption risk.
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="charges" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:1rem;color:#003087;">PTCL Bill Charges Explained</h2>
        <div style="display:grid;gap:0.8rem;">
          {[
            ["Line Rent / Subscription Charge", "Monthly fixed charge for your PTCL connection, paid regardless of usage. Varies by service type: basic landline, DSL package, or FlashFiber package subscription."],
            ["Local Call Charges", "Metered charges for calls made to PTCL landlines within your local exchange area."],
            ["National (NWD) Calls", "Charges for calls to other cities in Pakistan. NWD (National Wide Dialing) rates apply per minute."],
            ["International (IDD) Calls", "International call charges at IDD (International Direct Dialing) rates per minute by destination country."],
            ["Broadband Charges", "Fixed monthly fee for your DSL, FlashFiber, or CharJi internet package. May include excess data charges if you exceeded your bundle."],
            ["GST (19.5%)", "General Sales Tax on telecom services — higher than electricity/gas GST of 17%. Charged on all PTCL services."],
            ["Withholding Tax (WHT)", "Income Tax deducted at source — 12.5% for filers, 15% for non-filers. Applies to total PTCL bill."],
            ["Late Payment Surcharge", "10% of unpaid amount — only applies after 15-day grace period. Longest grace period of any Pakistani utility."],
          ].map(row => (
            <div style="background:#f8f9fa;border-radius:8px;padding:0.9rem 1.2rem;border-left:3px solid #003087;">
